# Musaium CODEOWNERS — security-critical paths require owner review
#
# Format: <pattern> <user/team>
# Last matching pattern wins. Place general rules first, specific rules last.
#
# This file enforces approval gates on security-critical, contract, and CI files.
# Created: 2026-04-07 (Tier 0 audit fix)
# Updated: 2026-04-26 (W0.2 SOC2 CC5/CC8 remediation — team-based ownership)
#
# How CODEOWNERS interacts with GitHub branch protection:
#   - This file alone does NOT enforce review. It declares default reviewers.
#   - Enforcement requires the branch protection rule:
#       Settings → Branches → Branch protection rule → "Require review from CODEOWNERS"
#   - Once enabled on `main` and `staging`, every PR touching a path listed
#     below will REQUIRE an approving review from the matching team/user
#     before merge can proceed.
#   - Solo-maintainer mode (2026-04-26): every rule resolves to @TimKraken.
#     Path structure preserved so team handles can be substituted later
#     (search/replace @TimKraken → @<team>) once contributors are added.
#   - See `docs/CONTRIBUTING.md` for the full PR review flow and required
#     status checks.

